⎩388⎭
⎩389⎭
  (literal) {⎩390⎭
      ⌈⎩391⎭
   Inside definitions only, pushes compiled literal to stack ⎩392⎭
⎩393⎭
       Certain Forth words are only applicable inside compiled sequences of subroutines ⎩394⎭
       Literals are handled in different ways when interpreted when in the REPL vs⎩395⎭
       compiled into sequences of subrs ⎩396⎭
       In the REPL, when we encounter a literal, we simply push it onto the stack ⎩397⎭
       In the compiler, though, we have to create an instruction that pushes ⎩398⎭
	 the literal onto the stack. ⎩399⎭
	 Compiled code doesn't do what the REPL does, we have to hard-wire and ⎩400⎭
	 bake in code that pushes the literal when the time comes to run the sequence. ⎩401⎭
⎩402⎭
       This word - "(literal)" - is a simple case and one could actually type this ⎩403⎭
	 instruction into the REPL, but, that would be redundant.  Other kinds of words, ⎩404⎭
	 e.g. some control-flow words, tend to be messier and the code below only handles ⎩405⎭
	 the compiled aspects and ignores the REPL aspects ⎩406⎭
⎩407⎭
       "IP" is the current word index in a sequence of words being compiled. ⎩408⎭
  ⌉⎩409⎭
      defsynonym lit ≡ State.RAM [State.IP]⎩410⎭
      %push (lit)⎩411⎭
      State.IP ⇐ State.IP + 1 ⌈ move past this item (the literal) - we're done with it ⌉⎩412⎭
  }⎩413⎭
⎩414⎭
  branch {⎩415⎭
      ⌈ This instruction appears only inside subroutine sequences, jump to address in next cell ⌉⎩416⎭
      ⌈ This instruction is inserted into a subr sequence when compiling control-flow words, like "else" see below) ⌉⎩417⎭
      State.IP ⇐ State.RAM [State.IP]⎩418⎭
      ⌈ normally, we just execute an instruction then move the IP sequentially forward by 1 unit, i.e. IP ⇐ IP + 1 ⌉⎩419⎭
      ⌈   in this case, though, we explicitly change the IP to some other value and don't just increment it ⌉⎩420⎭
  }⎩421⎭
⎩422⎭
  0branch {⎩423⎭
      ⌈ This instruction appears only inside subroutine sequences, jump on false to address in next cell ⌉⎩424⎭
      deftemp test ⇐ %toboolean (%pop)⎩425⎭
      if (test) {⎩426⎭
	  State.IP ⇐ State.IP + 1⎩427⎭
      } else {⎩428⎭
	 State.IP ⇐ State.RAM [State.IP]⎩429⎭
      }⎩430⎭
  }⎩431⎭
⎩432⎭
⎩433⎭
  ⌈ "immediate" words are fully operational even when in compile mode. Some (not all) of these words are meant to⎩434⎭
      work /only/ in compile mode. At the REPL prompt ("interpret" mode), they produce unwanted results.⎩435⎭
    immediate words: xif, xelse, xthen, xquote, xcomment, xsemi⎩436⎭
    immediate words that only have meaning in compile mode: xif, xelse, xthen, xsemi⎩437⎭
  ⌉⎩438⎭
⎩439⎭
⎩440⎭
  ⌈ IF, ELSE and THEN are "immediate" words - they should only be used inside of ":" (colon compiler) ⌉⎩441⎭
⎩442⎭
  ⌈ see diagram compiling-IF-THEN.drawio.png ⌉⎩443⎭
  %immediate ❲if❳ { ⎩444⎭
      ⌈ This instruction appears only inside subroutine sequences, ( f -- ) compile if test and branchFalse ⌉ ⎩445⎭
      ⌈ Step. 1: generate conditional branch to yet-unknown target1 ⌉ ⎩446⎭
      deftemp branchFalseAddress ⇐ %funcall _find ("0branch")⎩447⎭
      %ram+ (branchFalseAddress) ⌈ insert branch-if-false opcode (word) ⌉ ⎩448⎭
      %rpush (%RAMnext) ⌈ target1 onto r-stack as memo for later fixup ⌉ ⎩449⎭
      defsynonym target1 ≡ -1 ⎩450⎭
      %ram+ (target1) ⌈ branch target will be fixed up later ⌉ ⎩451⎭
      ⌈ Step. 2: generate code for true branch - return to compiler which will compile the following words ⌉ ⎩452⎭
      ⌈ THEN or ELSE will do the fixup of target1 ⌉ ⎩453⎭
  }⎩454⎭
⎩455⎭
  ⌈ see diagram compiling-IF-ELSE-THEN.drawio.png ⌉⎩456⎭
  %immediate ❲else❳ {⎩457⎭
      ⌈ Step. 1: fixup target1 from IF-true, retrieving memo from R-stack ⌉⎩458⎭
      deftemp target1 ⇐ %rpop⎩459⎭
      State.RAM [target1] ⇐ %RAMnext⎩460⎭
      ⌈ Step. 2: generate unconditional branch for preceding IF, creating new memo for target2 on R-stack ⌉⎩461⎭
      deftemp brAddress ⇐ %funcall _find ("branch")⎩462⎭
      %rpush (%RAMnext) ⌈ target2 address on R-stack as memo for later fixup ⌉⎩463⎭
      defsynonym target2 ≡ -1⎩464⎭
      %ram+ (target2) ⌈ branch target will be fixed up later ⌉⎩465⎭
      ⌈ Step. 3: generate code for false branch - return to compiler which will compile the following words ⌉⎩466⎭
      ⌈ THEN will do the fixup of target2 ⌉⎩467⎭
  }⎩468⎭
⎩469⎭
  ⌈ see diagrams compiling-IF-THEN.drawio.png and compiling-IF-ELSE-THEN.drawio.png ⌉⎩470⎭
  %immediate ❲then❳ {⎩471⎭
      ⌈ Step. 1: fixup target (from IF or from ELSE, above), retrieving memo from R-stack ⌉⎩472⎭
      deftemp target ⇐ %rpop⎩473⎭
      State.RAM [target] ⇐ %RAMnext⎩474⎭
  }⎩475⎭
⎩476⎭
  (do) {⎩477⎭
      ⌈ ( limit index --) Puts limit and index on return stack. ⌉⎩478⎭
      @xswap⎩479⎭
      deftemp index ⇐ %pop⎩480⎭
      deftemp limit ⇐ %pop⎩481⎭
      %rpush (index)⎩482⎭
      %rpush (limit)⎩483⎭
  }⎩484⎭
⎩485⎭
  %immediate ❲do❳ {⎩486⎭
      ⌈ (  limit index --) Begin counted loop. ⌉⎩487⎭
      %ram+(%funcall _find("(do)"))  ⌈ Push do loop handler. ⌉⎩488⎭
      %rpush(%RAMnext)           ⌈ Push address to jump back to. ⌉⎩489⎭
  }⎩490⎭
⎩491⎭
  (loop) {⎩492⎭
      ⌈ (  -- f) Determine if loop is done. ⌉⎩493⎭
      deftemp index ⇐ %rpop⎩494⎭
      deftemp limit ⇐ %rpop⎩495⎭
      defsynonym cond ≡ (index >= limit)⎩496⎭
      %push (cond)⎩497⎭
      if (cond) { ⌈ clean up rstack if index >= limit ⌉⎩498⎭
	  %rpop⎩499⎭
	  %rpop⎩500⎭
      }  ⎩501⎭
  }⎩502⎭
⎩503⎭
  %immediate +loop {⎩504⎭
      ⌈ ( --) Close counted loop. ⌉⎩505⎭
      %ram+(%funcall _find("(loop)"))   ⌈ Compile in loop test. ⌉⎩506⎭
      %ram+(%funcall _find("0branch"))  ⌈ Compile in branch check. ⌉⎩507⎭
      %ram+(%rpop)           ⌈ Address to jump back to. ⌉⎩508⎭
  }⎩509⎭
⎩510⎭
  %immediate ❲loop❳ {⎩511⎭
      ⌈ (  --) Close counted loop. ⌉⎩512⎭
      %push (1)⎩513⎭
      @literalize                  ⌈ Default loop increment for x_loop. ⌉⎩514⎭
      %ram+(%funcall _find("(loop)"))   ⌈ Compile in loop test. ⌉⎩515⎭
      %ram+(%funcall _find("0branch"))  ⌈ Compile in branch check. ⌉⎩516⎭
      %ram+(%rpop)           ⌈ Address to jump back to. ⌉⎩517⎭
  }⎩518⎭
⎩519⎭
  %immediate ❲begin❳ {⎩520⎭
      %rpush (%RAMnext)  ⌈ ( --) Start indefinite loop. ⌉⎩521⎭
  }⎩522⎭
⎩523⎭
  %immediate ❲until❳ {⎩524⎭
      ⌈ (  f --) Close indefinite loop with test. ⌉⎩525⎭
      %ram+(%funcall _find("0branch"))  ⌈ Expects result of test on stack. ⌉⎩526⎭
      %ram+(%rpop)           ⌈ Address to jump back to. ⌉⎩527⎭
  }⎩528⎭
⎩529⎭
⎩530⎭
⎩531⎭
  ⌈  "... 123 constant K ..." ⌉⎩532⎭
  ⌈  at interpretation time: 123 is on the Stack, we have consumed "constant" from BUFF, BUFF now contains "K ..." ⌉⎩533⎭
  ⌈  invoke 'word' which parses "K" and pushed it. The stack becomes [... 123 "K"] ⌉⎩534⎭
  ⌈  pop "K", pop 123, create a new word called 'K' with its PFA set to 123 and its CFA set to a subr that⎩535⎭
       gets 123 from its PFA and pushes it onto the stack ⌉⎩536⎭
  ❲const❳ {⎩537⎭
      ⌈  get next word - the name - from BUFF ⌉⎩538⎭
      defsynonym blank ≡ 32⎩539⎭
      %push (blank)⎩540⎭
      @xword⎩541⎭
      ⌈  stack is now: ( NNNN name -- ) ⌉⎩542⎭
      deftemp name ⇐ %pop⎩543⎭
      deftemp value ⇐ %pop⎩544⎭
      defsynonym normal ≡ 0⎩545⎭
      deftemp fobj ⇐ %funcall code (name, normal, ↪︎doconst)⎩546⎭
      %ram+ (value)⎩547⎭
  }⎩548⎭
⎩549⎭
  , {⎩550⎭
      %funcall comma (%pop)⎩551⎭
  }⎩552⎭
⎩553⎭
  variable {⎩554⎭
      defsynonym blank ≡ 32⎩555⎭
      %push (blank)⎩556⎭
      @xword⎩557⎭
      deftemp name ⇐ %pop⎩558⎭
      deftemp value ⇐ %pop⎩559⎭
      %funcall fvar (name, value)    ⎩560⎭
  }⎩561⎭
⎩562⎭
  dump {⎩563⎭
      deftemp n ⇐ %toint (%pop)⎩564⎭
      deftemp start ⇐ %toint (%pop)⎩565⎭
      %print ("----------------------------------------------------------------")⎩566⎭
      deftemp a ⇐ start⎩567⎭
      while (a < start + (%funcall min (n, (%funcall len (State.RAM) - start)))) {⎩568⎭
	  %print (a)⎩569⎭
	  %print (": ")⎩570⎭
	  %print (State.RAM [a])⎩571⎭
	  %eol⎩572⎭
	  deftemp a ⇐ a + 1⎩573⎭
      }⎩574⎭
  }⎩575⎭
⎩576⎭
  ! {⎩577⎭
      deftemp b ⇐ %pop⎩578⎭
      deftemp a ⇐ %pop⎩579⎭
      State.RAM [b] ⇐ a⎩580⎭
  }⎩581⎭
⎩582⎭
  bye { ⌈ ( --) Leave interpreter ⌉ %quit }⎩583⎭
⎩584⎭
⎩585⎭
  find {⎩586⎭
      ⌈ "( name | -- (name 0)|(xt 1)|(xt -1)) Search for word name." ⌉⎩587⎭
      ⌈ 3 possible results: 1. (name 0) if not found, 2. (xt 1) if found and word is immediate, 3. (xt -1) if found and word is normal ⌉⎩588⎭
      %push (32)⎩589⎭
      @xword⎩590⎭
      deftemp found ⇐ %funcall _find(%stop)⎩591⎭
      if (0 = found) {⎩592⎭
	  %push (0)⎩593⎭
      } else {⎩594⎭
	  %pop  ⌈ # Get rid of name on stack. ⌉⎩595⎭
	  %push(found)⎩596⎭
	  deftemp immediate ⇐ -1⎩597⎭
	  if (State.RAM[%stop - 1] & 1) { immediate ⇐ 1 }⎩598⎭
	  %push(immediate)⎩599⎭
      }⎩600⎭
  }⎩601⎭
⎩602⎭
  ' {⎩603⎭
      ⌈ "( name -- xt|-1) Search for execution token of word name." ⌉⎩604⎭
      %push (32)⎩605⎭
      @xword⎩606⎭
      deftemp name ⇐ %pop⎩607⎭
      deftemp found ⇐ %funcall _find(name)⎩608⎭
      %push (found)⎩609⎭
  }⎩610⎭
⎩611⎭
  None {⎩612⎭
      %pushNone⎩613⎭
  }⎩614⎭
⎩615⎭
  words {⎩616⎭
      ⌈ print words in dictionary ⌉⎩617⎭
      deftemp x ⇐ State.LAST⎩618⎭
      while (x > -1) {⎩619⎭
	  %print (State.RAM [x+ 1])⎩620⎭
	  %print (" ")⎩621⎭
      }⎩622⎭
      %eol⎩623⎭
  }⎩624⎭
⎩625⎭
⎩626⎭
  execute {⎩627⎭
      ⌈ invoke given word ⌉⎩628⎭
      deftemp wordAddress ⇐ %pop⎩629⎭
      @@wordAddress⎩630⎭
  }⎩631⎭
⎩632⎭
⎩633⎭
  : {⎩634⎭
      ⌈ ( name | --) Start compilation. ⌉⎩635⎭
      defsynonym blank ≡ 32⎩636⎭
      %push (blank)⎩637⎭
      @xword⎩638⎭
      deftemp name ⇐ %pop⎩639⎭
      %funcall code(name, 0, doword)⎩640⎭
      %setCompilingState⎩641⎭
  }⎩642⎭
⎩643⎭
  %immediate ; {⎩644⎭
      ⌈ ( --) Finish definition. ⌉⎩645⎭
⎩646⎭
      %ram+(-1)  ⌈ Marker for end of definition. ⌉⎩647⎭
      %setNotCompilingState⎩648⎭
  }⎩649⎭
⎩650⎭
  interpret {⎩651⎭
      ⌈ ( string --) Execute word. ⌉⎩652⎭
⎩653⎭
      @xfind⎩654⎭
      ⌈ 3 possible results from xfind:⎩655⎭
	  1. (name 0) if not found,⎩656⎭
	  2. (xt 1) if found and word is immediate,⎩657⎭
	  3. (xt -1) if found and word is normal ⌉⎩658⎭
      deftemp result ⇐ %pop					    defsynonym foundimmediate ≡ (result = 1)⎩659⎭
      deftemp item ⇐ %pop						    defsynonym foundnormal ≡ (result = -1)⎩660⎭
								      defsynonym notfound ≡ (result = 0)⎩661⎭
								      defsynonym found ≡ (foundimmediate or foundnormal)⎩662⎭
⎩663⎭
if (found) {⎩664⎭
    if (%incompilingstate) {⎩665⎭
        if (foundimmediate) {⎩666⎭
            λexec(item)⎩667⎭
        } else {⎩668⎭
            λcompileword(item)⎩669⎭
        }⎩670⎭
        ⎩671⎭
    } else {⎩672⎭
        λexec(item)⎩673⎭
    }⎩674⎭
    ⎩675⎭
} else {⎩676⎭
    if (%incompilingstate) {⎩677⎭
        if (%isinteger(item)) {⎩678⎭
            λcompileinteger(item)⎩679⎭
        } else {⎩680⎭
            if (%isfloat(item)) {⎩681⎭
                λcompilefloat(item)⎩682⎭
            } else {⎩683⎭
                @returnFalse⎩684⎭
            }⎩685⎭
            ⎩686⎭
        }⎩687⎭
        ⎩688⎭
    } else {⎩689⎭
        if (%isinteger(item)) {⎩690⎭
            λpushasinteger(item)⎩691⎭
        } else {⎩692⎭
            if (%isfloat(item)) {⎩693⎭
                λpushasfloat(item)⎩694⎭
            } else {⎩695⎭
                @returnFalse⎩696⎭
            }⎩697⎭
            ⎩698⎭
        }⎩699⎭
        ⎩700⎭
    }⎩701⎭
    ⎩702⎭
}⎩703⎭
⎩704⎭
      return True⎩705⎭
}⎩706⎭
}⎩707⎭
⎩708⎭
invoke {⎩709⎭
  @ok⎩710⎭
}⎩711⎭